<span id="freeTextContainer2684596898221520959">The conclusion of the trilogy and Moira and Cian&apos;s story.<br/><br/>The two were the couple I was most interested in from the beginning, as they started with animosity and the obstacles between them seemed insurmountable, which are two of my favorite tropes.<br/><br/>The war is imminent and our heroes are trying to prepare their army and themselves, while dealing with various attacks and mind games by the vampire queen, who&apos;s becoming more unhinged as time goes by. There are a few threads involving her that are dist</span>
  <span id="freeText2684596898221520959" style="display:none">The conclusion of the trilogy and Moira and Cian's story.<br /><br />The two were the couple I was most interested in from the beginning, as they started with animosity and the obstacles between them seemed insurmountable, which are two of my favorite tropes.<br /><br />The war is imminent and our heroes are trying to prepare their army and themselves, while dealing with various attacks and mind games by the vampire queen, who's becoming more unhinged as time goes by. There are a few threads involving her that are disturbing, <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[mostly the ones with Davey and the sick relationship between them <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>.<br /><br />Romance in time of war is never easy, but it's even harder for our heroes who know they can have no future despite the outcome of the war. Determined to make the best with the time they've got, when they succumb to each other, they give it their all and their relationship is intense.<br /><br />The war takes much out of everyone, but <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[our heroes together are victorious and Cain leaves when the battle is done, too emotionally involved to subject them both in a painful goodbye. They're both heartbroken and Cian doesn't see himself getting over Moira anytime soon, when Morrigan and the gods give him his much deserved reward, a choice between remaining as he is now or regaining his humanity. His choice is clear and leads to a happy ever after for all three couples <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>.<br /><br />Engaging story with ups and downs and a main thread that spans the whole trilogy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="2684596898221520959" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
